{"title_page": "Statista", "text_new": "{{Advert|date=August 2019}}\n{{Short description|German Internet company}}\n{{Infobox company\n|name              = Statista\n|logo              = Statista.png\n|key_people        = [[Friedrich Schwandt]] (CEO), Hubert Jakob (COO)\n|industry          = [[Database]]\n|foundation        = [[Hamburg]], Germany<br />({{start date and age|2007}})\n|location_country  = [[Hamburg, Germany]]\n|homepage          = {{URL|http://statista.com|statista.com}}\n}}\n\n'''Statista''' is a German [[online portal]] for [[statistics]], which makes data collected by market and [[opinion research]] institutes and data derived from the economic sector and official statistics available in English, French, German and Spanish. According to the company, its platform contains more than 1,000,000 statistics on more than 80,000 topics from more than 22,500 sources. The company states that it covers 170 different industries. According to Statista, the platform has more than 1.5 million users and generates a revenue of about \u20ac60 million.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.statista.com/aboutus/|title=Statista - The Statistics Portal|website=Statista}}</ref> Apart from statistics, Statista also provides data on market forecasts, white paper studies, dossiers, industry reports, digital market outlooks and consumer market outlooks.\n\n== History ==\nThe company was founded by Dr Friedrich Schwandt, Tim Kr\u00f6ger, Mattias Protzmann, Thilo L\u00f6we and Hubert Jakob in 2007, and it currently has more than 700 employees, including database experts, writers and statisticians. Statista does not only provide data in German but also in English, French and Spanish. Statista's head office is located at the Brahms Kontor in Hamburg; the company also has offices in New York, London, Paris and Singapore.<ref name=\"focus\">[https://statistacdn.s3.amazonaws.com/static/promo/Der_Herr_der_Daten.png FOCUS-Magazin: Der Herr der Daten]</ref> \nAccording to Statista, the portal's data partners include the [[Federal Statistical Office of Germany]] (Destatis), the [[Allensbach Institute]] (IfD Allensbach), the [[OECD]], the [[German Institute for Economic Research]] (DIW Berlin) and [[B\u00fcrgel]]. There are also partnerships with WELT, T-Online and the Handelszeitung.<ref name=\"statista\">{{cite web|url=http://www.statista.com/aboutus/|title=Statista - The Statistics Portal|website=Statista}}</ref>\nThe web site deutsche-startups.de named Statista \"Start-up of the Year\" in 2008<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.deutsche-startups.de/2008/12/15/statista-ist-das-start-up-des-jahres/|title=Statista ist das Start-up des Jahres - deutsche-startups.de|date=15 December 2008|publisher=}}</ref> and in the same year, the company was among the winners of the start-up competition \"Enable to Start\", sponsored by the Financial Times Germany. In 2010, the initiative \"Deutschland \u2013 Land der Ideen\" (Germany \u2013 Land of Ideas) selected Statista as one of the winners in the category \"Landmarks in the Land of Ideas 2010\".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.land-der-ideen.de/365-orte/preistraeger/statista|title=Deutschland Land der Ideen 2010|publisher=|url-status=dead|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120212162707/http://www.land-der-ideen.de/365-orte/preistraeger/statista|archive-date=2012-02-12|df=}}</ref> and awarded the European Red Herring Prize.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://207.204.3.140/RHE2010/rhe2010winners/rhe2010winners.html|title=Red Herring Europe Winners 2010|publisher=|url-status=dead|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140714131528/http://207.204.3.140/RHE2010/rhe2010winners/rhe2010winners.html |archive-date=2014-07-14|df=}}</ref>In 2012, Statista was nominated for the German Entrepreneur Award in the category \"Fast Climber\" , and in 2014, it was named Best Database by the Library Journal .\nAt the end of 2015, Statista was bought by advertising company Str\u00f6er Media.<ref name=\"statista\" />\n\n== Profile ==\nThe company provides statistics and survey results, which are presented in charts and tables. Its main target groups are business customers, lecturers and researchers. The data provided by the company cover, among other things, advertisement, buying behaviour or specific industries.\n\nStatista offers both free and paid content. In order to be able to use the data further, you need to register as a user, but diagrams can be viewed without registration. Users also have access to the Digital Market Outlook, the Consumer Market Outlook and the Mobility Market Outlook, which are based on demographic and economic data and give detailed insights into the development of the respective market. In-depth analyses of consumer behaviour and media usage can be carried out with the help of the Global Consumer Survey.<ref name=\"crl\">{{cite web|url=http://www.crl.edu/review/statista|title=Statista - eDesiderata|website=www.crl.edu}}</ref>\n\nIn addition to numerous individual statistics, there is a study database containing more than 41,000 studies . Customers can also contact Statista's Research & Analysis department to commission specific surveys, and the company produces individual infographics, videos or presentations and publications.\n\n==Infographics==\nSince the end of 2011, Statista produces free [[infographics]], which are published on a regular basis on news sites on current subjects from the areas of media and technology for downloading. These graphics are used by websites like [[Mashable]],<ref name=\"Mash\">{{cite web|url=http://mashable.com/2012/03/16/encyclopedia-britannica-wikipedia-infographic/|title=Encyclopedia Britannica vs. Wikipedia [INFOGRAPHIC]|first=Matt|last=Silverman|publisher=Mashable}}</ref> [[Business Insider]]<ref name=\"BI\">{{cite web|url=http://www.businessinsider.com/forbes-billionaires-list-infographic-2012-3|title=This Year's Forbes World's Billionaires List In One Simple Infographic|publisher=Business Insider}}</ref> or [[VentureBeat]].<ref name=\"VB\">{{cite web|url=https://venturebeat.com/2012/01/24/yahoos-fallback-position-hey-at-least-were-not-aol-numbers/|title=Yahoo's fallback position: Hey, at least we're not AOL (numbers) - VentureBeat|website=venturebeat.com}}</ref>\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n* [http://www.statista.com/ Homepage of Statista]\n* [https://www.libraryjournal.com/?detailStory=best-databases-best-reference-2015/ Library Journal review of Statista]\n* [https://howtonow.com/how-to-do-online-research-how-to-fact-check-verify-quotes-and-find-reliable-sources/#statista Is Statista a Reliable Source?]\n\n[[Category:Online companies of Germany]]\n[[Category:Companies based in Hamburg]]\n[[Category:Statistical organizations]]\n", "text_old": "{{Advert|date=August 2019}}\n{{Short description|German Internet company}}\n{{Infobox company\n|name              = Statista\n|logo              = Statista.png\n|key_people        = [[Friedrich Schwandt]] (CEO), Hubert Jakob (COO)\n|industry          = [[Database]]\n|foundation        = [[Hamburg]], Germany<br />({{start date and age|2007}})\n|location_country  = [[Hamburg, Germany]]\n|homepage          = {{URL|http://statista.com|statista.com}}\n}}\n\n'''Statista''' is a German [[online portal]] for [[statistics]], which makes data collected by market and [[opinion research]] institutes and data derived from the economic sector and official statistics available in English, French, German and Spanish. According to the company, its platform contains more than 1,000,000 statistics on more than 80,000 topics from more than 22,500 sources. The company states that it covers 170 different industries. According to Statista, the platform has more than 1.5 million users and generates a revenue of about \u20ac60 million.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.statista.com/aboutus/|title=Statista - The Statistics Portal|website=Statista}}</ref> Apart from statistics, Statista also provides data on market forecasts, white paper studies, dossiers, i