ta produces free infographics, which are published on a regular basis on news sites on current subjects from the areas of media and technology for downloading. These graphics are used by websites like [[Mashable]],<ref name=\"Mash\">{{cite web|url=http://mashable.com/2012/03/16/encyclopedia-britannica-wikipedia-infographic/|title=Encyclopedia Britannica vs. Wikipedia [INFOGRAPHIC]|first=Matt|last=Silverman|publisher=Mashable}}</ref> [[Business Insider]]<ref name=\"BI\">{{cite web|url=http://www.businessinsider.com/forbes-billionaires-list-infographic-2012-3|title=This Year's Forbes World's Billionaires List In One Simple Infographic|publisher=Business Insider}}</ref> or [[VentureBeat]].<ref name=\"VB\">{{cite web|url=https://venturebeat.com/2012/01/24/yahoos-fallback-position-hey-at-least-were-not-aol-numbers/|title=Yahoo's fallback position: Hey, at least we're not AOL (numbers) - VentureBeat|website=venturebeat.com}}</ref>\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n* [http://www.statista.com/ Homepage of Statista]\n* [https://www.libraryjournal.com/?detailStory=best-databases-best-reference-2015/ Library Journal review of Statista]\n* [https://howtonow.com/how-to-do-online-research-how-to-fact-check-verify-quotes-and-find-reliable-sources/#statista Is Statista a Reliable Source?]\n\n[[Category:Online companies of Germany]]\n[[Category:Companies based in Hamburg]]\n[[Category:Statistical organizations]]\n", "name_user": "Kku", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eInfographics:l", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Statista"}
